cs.LG, cs.AR, cs.CV, cs.SY, cs.NE 

This paper is primarily focused on the performance analysis and characterization of training deep learning models on mobile devices. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper also discusses the use of convolutional neural networks and recurrent neural networks, which are commonly used in computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL) tasks, respectively. The paper also discusses the use of hardware utilization and power consumption, which falls under the sub-categories of cs.AR (Hardware Architecture) and cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the paper discusses the use of fine-grained operations in deep learning models, which is related to the sub-category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
